"Semur","type":"LAST","attribution":"Dictionary of American Family Names © Patrick Hanks 2003, 2006.","meanings":["German: variant of   Siemer  ."],"variants":[{"name":"Siemer","meanings":["Some characteristic forenames:  German Helmut, Helmuth, Otto, Theresia.","German: from the ancient Germanic personal name <i>Siegmar</i>, composed of the elements <i>sigi</i> ‘victory’ + <i>mari</i>, <i>meri</i> ‘famous’."]}]},{"name":"Dalmas","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Mainly U.S.: transferred use of the surname, adopted in honour of  George Mifflin Dallas , Vice-President  1845–49 , after whom the city in Texas is named. The surname is of Scottish origin, derived from the village of Dallas in Morayshire, named in Gaelic as <i>Dalfhas</i> ‘meadow stance’, i.e. a meadow traditionally used as a night's resting place by cattle drovers."],"variants":[]}],"lifeSummary":"Dalmas de Semur II was born about 1130, in Charolles, Charolles, Saône-et-Loire, Bourgogne-Franche-Comté, France as the son of Geoffroy de Semur-en-Brionnais III or  VI and Dame Emma de Sémur. He had at least 2 sons with N de Bourbon-Lancy. In 1162, at the age of 33, his occupation is listed as seigneur de semur en brionnais. He died in 1190, in Semur-en-Brionnais, Saône-et-Loire, Burgundy, France, at the age of 61."},"et":{"environ 1130–1190":"umbes 1130–1190","1128–Male":"1128–Surnud","1130–1190":"1130–1190","–Female":"Surnud","1162–1226":"1162–1226","1165–1219":"1165–1219","1109–1150":"1109–1150","ABT 1150":"umbes 1150","1190":"1190","1128":"1128","1226":"1226","environ 1130":"umbes 1130","1165":"1165","1130":"1130","1162":"1162","1150":"1150","1109":"1109","1219":"1219","Semur-en-Brionnais, Saône-et-Loire, Bourgogne, France":"Semur-en-Brionnais, Saône-et-Loire, Bourgogne, Prantsusmaa","Semur-en-Brionnais, Charolles, Saône-et-Loire, Bourgogne-Franche-Comté, France":"Charolles, Charolles, Saône-et-Loire, Bourgogne-Franche-